---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { UserButton as ClerkUserButton } from '@clerk/astro/components';
---

<Base
  title="Validation tooling | Silicon Crane"
  description="Silicon Crane validation tooling preview."
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-slate-50">
    <header class="bg-white border-b border-slate-200">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between">
        <a href="/" class="font-bold text-slate-900">Silicon Crane</a>
        <ClerkUserButton />
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-blue-600 mb-3 font-mono">
        Private alpha — validation tooling
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 tracking-tight">
        Welcome to the validation tooling.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mb-12 leading-relaxed">
        This is the operator surface we use to ship and measure structured product
        experiments. You are seeing the alpha — features land here as we build them
        for our own engagements.
      </p>

      <section class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200">
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Experiments</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Distill brief, archetype, kill criteria, and copy pack — every experiment
            tracked from hypothesis to decision memo.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 font-mono">archetype: waitlist | priced_waitlist | presale | service_pilot | content_magnet | concierge | interview</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200">
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Leads</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Every signup, every event, attributed to its experiment. Conversion
            rates roll up to the lifecycle stage.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 font-mono">stages: draft → preflight → build → launch → run → decide → archive</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200">
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">Decisions</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Decision memos, learning memos, kill-or-double-down. The output of the
            experiment is the next decision, not just the data.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 font-mono">decision_memos | learning_memos</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-16 bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-slate-200">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">In active development</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The full UI for these flows is coming online iteratively. The data model
          is live (sc-api `/experiments`, `/leads`, `/events`, `/metrics` endpoints
          all serve real data). What you do not yet see in this preview, you can
          reach via the API directly.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">
          Have a hypothesis you want to validate?
          <a href="mailto:launch@siliconcrane.com" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">launch@siliconcrane.com</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
